{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":774,"text":"I'm turning 44 next month,"},{"time":3190,"text":"and I have the sense that 44\nis going to be a very good year,"},{"time":7694,"text":"a year of fulfillment, realization."},{"time":11532,"text":"I have that sense,"},{"time":12919,"text":"not because of anything\nparticular in store for me,"},{"time":15990,"text":"but because I read it would be a good year"},{"time":18774,"text":"in a 1968 book by Norman Mailer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":22497,"text":"\"He felt his own age, forty-four ...\""},{"time":25473,"text":"wrote Mailer in \"The Armies of the Night,\""},{"time":28415,"text":"\"... felt as if he were a solid embodiment"},{"time":30901,"text":"of bone, muscle, heart, mind,\nand sentiment to be a man,"},{"time":34695,"text":"as if he had arrived.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":37207,"text":"Yes, I know Mailer\nwasn't writing about me."},{"time":40295,"text":"But I also know that he was;"},{"time":42617,"text":"for all of us -- you, me,\nthe subject of his book,"},{"time":46615,"text":"age more or less in step,"},{"time":48849,"text":"proceed from birth\nalong the same great sequence:"},{"time":53224,"text":"through the wonders\nand confinements of childhood;"},{"time":56425,"text":"the emancipations\nand frustrations of adolescence;"},{"time":60380,"text":"the empowerments\nand millstones of adulthood;"},{"time":64188,"text":"the recognitions\nand resignations of old age."},{"time":68391,"text":"There are patterns to life,"},{"time":70317,"text":"and they are shared."},{"time":72230,"text":"As Thomas Mann wrote:\n\"It will happen to me as to them.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":77772,"text":"We don't simply live these patterns."},{"time":80013,"text":"We record them, too."},{"time":81766,"text":"We write them down in books,\nwhere they become narratives"},{"time":84997,"text":"that we can then read and recognize."},{"time":87669,"text":"Books tell us who we've been,"},{"time":89984,"text":"who we are, who we will be, too."},{"time":93492,"text":"So they have for millennia."},{"time":96162,"text":"As James Salter wrote,"},{"time":97829,"text":"\"Life passes into pages\nif it passes into anything.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":102979,"text":"And so six years ago,\na thought leapt to mind:"},{"time":106372,"text":"if life passed into pages,\nthere were, somewhere,"},{"time":110327,"text":"passages written about every age."},{"time":112711,"text":"If I could find them, I could\nassemble them into a narrative."},{"time":116315,"text":"I could assemble them into a life,"},{"time":118377,"text":"a long life, a hundred-year life,"},{"time":121147,"text":"the entirety of that same great sequence"},{"time":123464,"text":"through which the luckiest among us pass."},{"time":127321,"text":"I was then 37 years old,"},{"time":130613,"text":"\"an age of discretion,\"\nwrote William Trevor."},{"time":135074,"text":"I was prone to meditating on time and age."},{"time":138322,"text":"An illness in the family\nand later an injury to me"},{"time":141189,"text":"had long made clear that growing old\ncould not be assumed."},{"time":145056,"text":"And besides, growing old\nonly postponed the inevitable,"},{"time":148715,"text":"time seeing through\nwhat circumstance did not."},{"time":151947,"text":"It was all a bit disheartening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":154413,"text":"A list, though, would last."},{"time":157334,"text":"To chronicle a life\nyear by vulnerable year"},{"time":160503,"text":"would be to clasp and to ground\nwhat was fleeting,"},{"time":163764,"text":"would be to provide myself and others\na glimpse into the future,"},{"time":167131,"text":"whether we made it there or not."},{"time":169574,"text":"And when I then began to compile my list,\nI was quickly obsessed,"},{"time":173685,"text":"searching pages and pages\nfor ages and ages."},{"time":177702,"text":"Here we were at every annual step\nthrough our first hundred years."},{"time":182624,"text":"\"Twenty-seven ... a time\nof sudden revelations,\""},{"time":187048,"text":"\"sixty-two, ... of subtle diminishments.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":191989,"text":"I was mindful, of course,\nthat such insights were relative."},{"time":196405,"text":"For starters, we now live longer,\nand so age more slowly."},{"time":201151,"text":"Christopher Isherwood used\nthe phrase \"the yellow leaf\""},{"time":204335,"text":"to describe a man at 53,"},{"time":206510,"text":"only one century after Lord Byron\nused it to describe himself at 36."}]},{"cues":[{"time":210853,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":213154,"text":"I was mindful, too, that life\ncan swing wildly and unpredictably"},{"time":216797,"text":"from one year to the next,"},{"time":218609,"text":"and that people may experience\nthe same age differently."},{"time":222045,"text":"But even so, as the list coalesced,"},{"time":225643,"text":"so, too, on the page, clear\nas the reflection in the mirror,"},{"time":229056,"text":"did the life that I had been living:"},{"time":231710,"text":"finding at 20 that \"... one is less\nand less sure of who one is;\""},{"time":236002,"text":"emerging at 30 from the \"... wasteland\nof preparation into active life;\""},{"time":241057,"text":"learning at 40 \"... to close softly\nthe doors to rooms"},{"time":245197,"text":"[I would] not be coming back to.\""},{"time":248720,"text":"There I was."}]},{"cues":[{"time":251885,"text":"Of course, there we all are."},{"time":254762,"text":"Milton Glaser, the great graphic designer"},{"time":257224,"text":"whose beautiful\nvisualizations you see here,"},{"time":260519,"text":"and who today is 85 --"},{"time":262403,"text":"all those years \"... a ripening\nand an apotheosis,\" wrote Nabokov --"},{"time":267211,"text":"noted to me that, like art and like color,"},{"time":271455,"text":"literature helps us to remember\nwhat we've experienced."}]},{"cues":[{"time":275095,"text":"And indeed, when I shared\nthe list with my grandfather,"},{"time":278857,"text":"he nodded in recognition."},{"time":281339,"text":"He was then 95 and soon to die,"},{"time":285234,"text":"which, wrote Roberto Bola√±o,"},{"time":287379,"text":"\"... is the same as never dying.\""},{"time":291556,"text":"And looking back, he said to me that, yes,"},{"time":295357,"text":"Proust was right that at 22,\nwe are sure we will not die,"},{"time":301873,"text":"just as a thanatologist\nnamed Edwin Shneidman was right"},{"time":304678,"text":"that at 90, we are sure we will."},{"time":309229,"text":"It had happened to him,"},{"time":311234,"text":"as to them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":315479,"text":"Now the list is done:"},{"time":318169,"text":"a hundred years."},{"time":321443,"text":"And looking back over it,"},{"time":324298,"text":"I know that I am not done."},{"time":326800,"text":"I still have my life to live,"},{"time":328919,"text":"still have many more pages to pass into."},{"time":332546,"text":"And mindful of Mailer,"},{"time":334422,"text":"I await 44."}]},{"cues":[{"time":336746,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":337948,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}